    <abstract>
      <t>&lt;p&gt;IEEE 802.1Qca Path Control and Reservation (PCR) specifies explicit path control via IS-IS in Layer 2 networks in order to move beyond the shortest path capabilities provided by IEEE 802.1aq Shortest Path Bridging (SPB).  IS-IS PCR provides capabilities for the establishment and control of explicit forwarding trees in a Layer 2 network domain.  This document specifies the sub-TLVs for IS-IS PCR.&lt;/p&gt;</t>
